                </svg>
            </a>
        </h4>
        <p>
            Restaurant website developed with .Net 6.0 Web API, EntityFramework 6, PostgreSQL 14, Angular 13 and Bootstrap 5.
        </p>
        <p>
            Customers can view menus, put them in their cart and place orders.<br/>
            Managers can set the website's general configurations along with managing categories, menus and orders.
        </p>
        <hr/>
        <p>
            I learned how Angular works and how it communicates with the backend APIs developed with .Net Web API.
            While working on this project, I also learned about RxJs, different HTTP methods and status codes, various CSS frameworks, containerizing with Docker, and AWS services for deployment.
        </p>
        <p>
            I was initially going to implement Swagger and Auth0 instead of using built-in EF user management, so the backend was developed with that in mind, but due to lack of time (<i>I don't want to lose the chance of applying to your company!</i>), these features are left behind for now, but will be added afterwards.
        </p>
    </div>
